<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4486501>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 11. — Eryma quadriverrucatum Trautschold, 1866 and its synonyms from the Tithonian of Russia: A, B, original figures of Trautschold (1866: pl. 3, fig. 5) of the holotype from Choroshowo: lateral view (A), dorsal view (B); C, original figure of Gerasimov (1955: pl. 8, fig. 3) from Ryazan; D, original figure of Gerasimov (1955: pl. 8, fig. 1) from Ryazan; E, F, original figures of Lahusen (1894: pl. 1, fig. 6) of one of the syntypes of Eryma mosquensis from Mneviki: dorsal view (E), ventral view (F); G, original figure of Gerasimov et al. (1995: pl. 4, fig. 9) from Moscow; H, original figure of Gerasimov et al. (1995: pl. 4, fig. 8) from Moscow; I, original figure of Gerasimov et al. (1995: pl. 4, fig. 10) from Moscow. Scale bars: 1 cm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4486501/files/figure.png" .

